<main id="main">

	<div class="container">

		<div class="row topspace">
			<div class="col-sm-8 col-sm-offset-2">

 				<article class="post">
					<header class="entry-header">
 						<div class="entry-meta">
 							<span class="posted-on"><time class="entry-date published">2020, updated in 2022</time></span>
 						</div>
 						<h1 class="lead text-center">Ecological trail</h1>
					</header>
					<div class="entry-content">
						<p><img alt="" src="proj3/3.jpg"></p>
						<p>
							I was born in Ufa city in Bashkortostan Republic known for its location between South Ural Mountains and Russian Plain.
							My family have a country house not very far from the city. A funny coicidience is that this village and its neighborhood turned out to be
							described in books of Sergey Aksakov, a famous Russian writer. <br><br>
							And there is a reason for it. This region is truly stunning as broad fields here meet shady forests. Cows and sheeps, horses from the horsefarm,
							ancient willows, grasslands and river. All of this makes you believe that you are in amazing fairytale.<br><br>
							Well, besides loud words, the region is a scientifically valuable as some of landscapes and plant complexes are unique.
							That is why I got an idea to create a ecological trail of not only beautiful views and activities, but also an educational option.
						</p>
						<p>
							There are some publications on this topic, inlcuding my own: <br>
							<a href="https://www.researchgate.net/publication/355439941_Landsaftnoe_obosnovanie_formirovania_osobo_ohranaemyh_prirodnyh_territorij_R_Baskortostan_Landscape_justification_for_creation_of_natural_reserves_Bashkortostan">about landscapes</a>, 
						</p>
						<p>
							In addition, just for my own pleasure, I decided to develop a creative map of a route that I could propose to visitors.
						</p>
						<h1 class="lead text-center">What did I do?</h1>
						<p>
							I took a very simple and ordinary satellite image of Yandex (zoom 14)
						</p>
						<p>
							<img src="proj3/1.jpg">
						</p>
						<p>
							Using it as a basemap, I outlined forest, grassland, villages and roads that may be used to drive to the area of interest. <br><br>
							My concept focuses on Bairamtau hill, as it was called in Aksakov's memoirs. The top of the hill provides a good viewpoint. 
						</p>
						<p>
							<img src="proj3/1.jpg">
						</p>
						<p>
							Then I marked sightseeing spots and drew a route through them, so that it could cover the most different landscapes.
						</p>
						<p>
							<img src="proj3/2.jpg"><br>
						</p>
						<p>
							One significant problem for me was the lack of a bridge to cross the river. The south bank is very beautiful, although it is not connected with
							the main part of the territory. The bridge in Novomikhailovka village was ruined in 1999 (or even earlier), so since then the closest way to get to the south bank is
							the bridge in Bochkarevka village (not in the picture) in 4500 m down the river. However, the old bridge piers of Novomikhailovka still stand safe and sound (more or less).
							So I decided to dream a little bit and imagine that this bridge is already reconstructed. In such case, other spots may be added to the route map.
						</p>
						<p>
							Afterwards, I needed just to add some design features to the map. For that I used Adobe Illustrator. Here I wanted to emphasize in which point
							you can find particular activity.
						</p>
						<h1 class="lead text-center">Check out the result!</h1>
						<p>
							<img src="proj3/2.jpg">
						</p>
					</div>
				</article>

			</div>
		</div>

		
